snippet.textDisplay:
Stay strong and safe, Italian friends! A few tips to share since I went on self-isolation with my families for the past 45 days just that I returned to work 2 weeks ago myself. None of my families and people around me have been infected so far.
1. Self-isolation is extremely boring - after two weeks you'd feel such boredom is driving you nuts. But keep staying the heck at home and don't go out. Take this precious time to read some of your favorite books, spend time with your children or parents, play some silly games with your loved ones - if there's no such game, invent one.
2. Pregnant women are most vulnerable because they can't be treated with any kind of medicine. And remember their future babies will most likely contract the virus if they themselves have been infected (it’s proven). People don't understand how dangerous the situation is for these women. I know this because my wife is expecting a baby early April. She hasn't stepped out of our home for so long that her body check yesterday didn't show good signs - confinement plus a little bit depression are very toxic I suppose.
3. Taking hot shower or bath or even sauna definitely help kill the virus. Test results prove that coronavirus can and will be killed when temperature exceeds 54 degree Celsius. This is a cheap and quite available method for most people - and very effective. When you take the hot bath, please try to breathe in hot air (not too hot though) and soak yourself in hot water for as long as you enjoy.
4. As there is no cure or vaccine, your own immune system is your most reliable defence as well as your last stand. To increase your immune system is what you need to do. Forget about your plan of losing weight and eat and sleep well. Without at least 7 hours sleep, your immune system won’t be strong and healthy enough. Drink a lot of milk, eat a lot of meat (chicken soup is very good meal at this critical time, banana will be cathartic to deal with constipation), and don’t do a lot of exercise to stress yourself out unless you are a pro athlete. One thing worth pointing out is that an immune system that’s too strong may not be very helpful in the fight against the virus because it may overact or overkill – it means a very healthy person can’t be too confident.
5. When you go out, face mask is a must. It’s not only for protecting yourself but also others. Some people may wear two layers of disposable mask thinking it’s safer. Don’t. Wearing two masks only forces the air to squeeze in from all corners of your masks instead of passing through.
6. Besides facial masks, disposable gloves and glasses are also helpful. The reason why coronavirus is extremely contagious is because it infects people from all possible ways – air, eyes, contact. So don’t rub your eyes or mouth when you are at a risky place. And keep one meter away from any strangers.
7. If you don’t have hand sanitizer or medical alcohol, no panic. You can simply use table salt to make your own sanitizer or disinfectant because the salt’s crystal structure can pierce or at least weaken the outer jelly layer of the virus. And if you are running short of masks, you can use salty water to wash your used mask and then hang it dry under the sunshine for reuse.
8. The typical CT scanned image of the infected lungs resemble frosted glass. So if nucleic acid test isn’t available, CT scan is also useful and can be quite accurate.
9. The coronavirus symptom is not limited to lungs though. It may also affect liver and heart. A few patients in China were seen drop-dead because of the acute myocarditis resulted from the virus. And there’s an omnipresent fatigue for the patients. So those who already have illness in those parts of the body should be more cautious.
Anyway, just my two cents. Hope this virus may die down soon and return a better Earth to us all. I am from Guangzhou, China and welcome you all to visit my town when better time comes again 😊
